<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05019i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05019i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05019i"> 19(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> BVM&apos;s consent necessary</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> In a host of their devotional books, intended for women and girls as well as men, it is said that <mark>Mary&apos;s consent was necessary</mark> before the miracle of the Incarnation could be possible. &ldquo;The Holy Ghost,&rdquo; says Avrillon, &ldquo;vouchsafed to await her consent ere working within her chaste womb the Incarnation of the Word.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [A Virgin Mother] 177</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
